The store, located at Adlife Plaza in Kilimani, is stocking office and casual men's wear as well as women accessories.&ldquo;I am excited to provide men with an alternative. We are bringing the fashion experience closer to men. Our clients don&rsquo;t need to be outside the country to purchase their favourites designers' wear,&rdquo; Pulei, who is President Uhuru Kenyatta's stylist, said. &ldquo;Catering to the fashion tastes and preferences of the African man is no small fete, and at Naneulashan Apparel, we have found what the African man will want in his wardrobe.&rdquo; The signature style of the house will always be mixing the latest international trends and local cultures.